  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The safety and effectiveness of the &quot;mini-dose&quot; Bier block, a technique of i.v. regional
      anesthesia using low-dose lidocaine (1.5 mg/kg) without routine premedication, was evaluated
      in the emergency department treatment of pediatric upper extremity fractures and
      dislocations.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      this study aimed at comparing IVRA with small dose lidocaine and forearm tourniquet with
      conventional IVRA with arm tourniquet and usual lidocaine dose
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
